OL,3,CMystery of how giant galaxies formed
OL,4,Ccould be close to being solved
OL,6,FWorking with the Purple Mountain
OL,7,FObservatory in China and the Chinese
OL,8,FAcademy of Science, the team has
OL,9,Fanalysed more than 100 star-forming
OL,10,Fgalaxies in the distant universe using
OL,11,Fthe world's largest radio telescope,
OL,12,Fknown as Alma, in Chile's Atacama
OL,13,Fdesert.
OL,15,FStudy lead Dr Qing-Hua Tan, from the
OL,16,FPurple Mountain Observatory, said that
OL,17,Fthe research used a new technique
OL,18,Fwhich looked at the distribution of
OL,19,Flight emitted by distant and highly-
OL,20,Fluminous galaxies.
